  "body": "***Type***: Bug\r\n\r\n***Summary***: App starts to lag and becomes almost unusable when Group Chat member receives a message. Heavy lags happening because of continuous requests to mailsever for offline inbox message (visible by very frequent `Fetching messages...` label appearance and logs).\r\n\r\n**Note**: it doesn't matter whether the contact was a Group Chat admin or non-admin. It depends who from two contacts initiated a contact request between two. The one who receives a contact request with further group chat creation affected. But it'll be OK on the side of contact request initiator. See steps to reproduce:\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nNo app freezes when group chat member receives a message\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nApp freezes when group chat member receives a message\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status on two devices and create two accounts (Contact1 and Contact2)\r\n- Contact1 sends a contact request to Contact2\r\n- Contact1 creates a group chat with Contact2\r\n- Contact1 sends a text message in Group Chat\r\n- Contact2 observes app behaviour navigating between different screens\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: Develop (nightly 402nd Jenkins build) (it's **fine** on 401st nightly develop build)\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\nTF session of Contact2 in above scenario(it received 10 messages in Group chat and 1 message in 1-1 chat):  https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8352442/sessions/73/?accessToken=TJ1nAcW/cqBe94uNthMoX603JDQ\n\n<blockquote><div><strong><a href=\"https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8352442/sessions/73/?accessToken=TJ1nAcW/cqBe94uNthMoX603JDQ\">TestFairy: Status build-6006+ (6006) @73</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
